1
00:00:00,959 --> 00:00:02,293
[Oliver] <i>They'll support you, too, sir.</i>

2
00:00:02,377 --> 00:00:04,129
<i>Just watch your back.</i>

3
00:00:04,212 --> 00:00:06,172
<i>Whoever is covering up the evidence,</i>

4
00:00:06,256 --> 00:00:07,924
<i>I'm sure they'll target you.</i>

5
00:00:08,008 --> 00:00:09,009
<i>Oliver…</i>

6
00:00:09,092 --> 00:00:11,052
[tense music]

7
00:00:11,136 --> 00:00:14,139
[both grunting]

8
00:00:15,390 --> 00:00:17,100
- Oliver!
- [grunts]

9
00:00:18,101 --> 00:00:20,562
- [faint gunshots]
- [Oliver] <i>I'm sorry, sir.</i>

10
00:00:20,645 --> 00:00:22,439
<i>I won't be able to testify…</i>

11
00:00:22,522 --> 00:00:23,732
<i>so that we can right the wrong.</i>

12
00:00:25,066 --> 00:00:27,027
[Marcus] <i>My friends died because of me.</i>

13
00:00:27,110 --> 00:00:30,321
[Teresa] <i>I know you.</i>
<i>You will find justice for them.</i>

14
00:00:30,405 --> 00:00:32,949
<i>Just keep your promise to me, son.</i>

15
00:00:33,033 --> 00:00:34,784
<i>That nothing bad will happen to you.</i>

16
00:00:34,868 --> 00:00:37,037
<i>I can't bear to lose another son.</i>

17
00:00:37,620 --> 00:00:38,997
Jalil!

18
00:00:39,080 --> 00:00:40,790
[woman] Praise be to Allah!

19
00:00:41,374 --> 00:00:43,918
Jamillah, what happened?

20
00:00:44,002 --> 00:00:45,795
[tense music]

21
00:00:45,879 --> 00:00:47,380
[Jamillah sniffles]

22
00:00:52,594 --> 00:00:55,555
[mysterious theme music playing]

23
00:01:08,276 --> 00:01:11,362
Everyone thinks that you are dead.

24
00:01:12,322 --> 00:01:14,699
I didn't tell a soul where you are.

25
00:01:16,534 --> 00:01:20,580
Because I'd lose it
if the cops got you too.

26
00:01:22,040 --> 00:01:23,124
Where's Father?

27
00:01:26,878 --> 00:01:28,755
Where is Father?

28
00:01:31,341 --> 00:01:32,592
They arrested him.

29
00:01:33,301 --> 00:01:35,220
[grim music playing]

30
00:01:35,887 --> 00:01:36,763
They put him in jail.

31
00:01:41,559 --> 00:01:42,435
Why…

32
00:01:45,605 --> 00:01:47,190
[tense music]

33
00:01:47,273 --> 00:01:49,734
Why did they do this?

34
00:01:51,653 --> 00:01:55,573
Why did they have to disturb our peace?

35
00:02:01,704 --> 00:02:04,999
Why did they kill our neighbors?!

36
00:02:07,168 --> 00:02:08,336
Why?

37
00:02:09,671 --> 00:02:11,172
Why?!

38
00:02:11,798 --> 00:02:15,677
[breathing deeply]

39
00:02:16,427 --> 00:02:22,809
[grim music continues]

40
00:02:22,892 --> 00:02:23,852
This man…

41
00:02:25,979 --> 00:02:27,772
[music turns stirring]

42
00:02:28,857 --> 00:02:31,276
[Jalil sighs]

43
00:02:35,947 --> 00:02:38,241
- [gunshot]
- [both grunting]

44
00:02:40,368 --> 00:02:42,412
He's their leader.

45
00:02:44,622 --> 00:02:47,792
The man who destroyed our community…

46
00:02:50,628 --> 00:02:53,298
killed our neighbors…

47
00:02:53,381 --> 00:02:57,802
[tense music]

48
00:02:58,761 --> 00:03:00,889
…and arrested Father.

49
00:03:07,103 --> 00:03:09,147
[stirring music continues]

50
00:03:11,900 --> 00:03:13,902
- [officer] Sir, please wait outside.
- [reporter] He's here!

51
00:03:13,985 --> 00:03:15,820
Agent Reyes!

52
00:03:15,904 --> 00:03:18,573
Why did you order the massacre
of the children and the women?!

53
00:03:18,656 --> 00:03:20,241
[female reporter]
Do you have a grudge against Datu Rahman?

54
00:03:20,325 --> 00:03:22,493
[male reporter] Do you have a personal
vendetta against them, Agent Reyes?

55
00:03:22,577 --> 00:03:24,203
- [male reporter] Give us a comment, sir!
- [female reporter] Agent Reyes!

56
00:03:24,287 --> 00:03:27,290
- [female reporter] Is this true, Agent?
- [male reporter] Can you confirm it?

57
00:03:28,333 --> 00:03:30,543
[melancholic music playing]

58
00:03:34,130 --> 00:03:38,676
[fire crackling]

59
00:03:38,760 --> 00:03:42,013
[gunshots]

60
00:03:51,648 --> 00:03:56,819
[melancholic music continues]

61
00:04:10,083 --> 00:04:13,461
[camera shutters clicking]

62
00:04:16,631 --> 00:04:19,175
[music becomes stirring]

63
00:04:33,398 --> 00:04:37,777
[somber music]

64
00:04:51,082 --> 00:04:52,083
Jalil!

65
00:04:52,917 --> 00:04:54,043
Jalil…

66
00:04:55,211 --> 00:04:56,087
You're alive?

67
00:04:59,257 --> 00:05:00,758
Wha… What happened to you?

68
00:05:02,343 --> 00:05:03,803
I'm glad you're alive.

69
00:05:04,595 --> 00:05:05,847
Praise be to Allah.

70
00:05:07,724 --> 00:05:11,769
Jalil. We all know their accusations
against your father aren't true.

71
00:05:13,604 --> 00:05:15,815
You have to save Datu Rahman.

72
00:05:16,399 --> 00:05:18,359
I'm going to fix all this.

73
00:05:20,194 --> 00:05:21,529
I'm sure…

74
00:05:22,530 --> 00:05:24,282
that Father is innocent.

75
00:05:29,162 --> 00:05:32,373
They just dragged us into this mess
knowing we'd be the easiest to blame.

76
00:05:33,583 --> 00:05:35,626
But I will not stop…

77
00:05:36,919 --> 00:05:41,215
until I get revenge for our neighbors.

78
00:05:45,261 --> 00:05:47,346
Mark my words.

79
00:05:48,014 --> 00:05:49,599
Mark my words!

80
00:05:50,224 --> 00:05:52,268
I'll make it happen!

81
00:05:52,351 --> 00:05:54,645
[stirring music playing]

82
00:06:04,530 --> 00:06:10,828
[protesters chanting]
Justice! Justice! Justice!

83
00:06:10,912 --> 00:06:14,749
[female activist] We won't
allow injustice to prevail!

84
00:06:15,333 --> 00:06:16,250
[female activisit] Justice for Datu!

85
00:06:16,334 --> 00:06:17,460
[crowd] Justice!

86
00:06:17,543 --> 00:06:20,004
Free Datu Rahman!

87
00:06:20,088 --> 00:06:21,506
[crowd] Free him!

88
00:06:21,589 --> 00:06:25,551
[female activist]
You murderers! You killed our families!

89
00:06:25,635 --> 00:06:28,262
- [crowd] Murderers!
- Justice for Zamboanga!

90
00:06:28,346 --> 00:06:29,597
[crowd] Justice!

91
00:06:29,680 --> 00:06:31,682
[chants] Justice!

92
00:06:31,766 --> 00:06:34,727
[protesters chanting]
Justice! Justice! Justice!

93
00:06:34,811 --> 00:06:37,688
Justice! Justice!

94
00:06:37,772 --> 00:06:39,232
Justice!

95
00:06:41,859 --> 00:06:43,069
[gloomy music playing]

96
00:06:43,152 --> 00:06:44,862
- [grunts]
- [wet thud]

97
00:06:47,073 --> 00:06:48,658
[faint gunshots]

98
00:06:53,037 --> 00:06:55,331
[gloomy music continues]

99
00:06:58,835 --> 00:07:00,545
[Marcus] Oliver! Oliver!

100
00:07:00,628 --> 00:07:02,296
- [wheezes]
- Nurse!

101
00:07:02,380 --> 00:07:04,590
Nurse! Help!

102
00:07:07,385 --> 00:07:10,388
[Marcus] <i>Oliver! Oliver!</i>

103
00:07:11,806 --> 00:07:15,977
[glomy music continues]

104
00:07:31,826 --> 00:07:35,496
[music becomes stirring]

105
00:07:47,133 --> 00:07:49,385
[gunshots]

106
00:07:56,684 --> 00:07:58,936
Sir, the police already
looked through these yesterday.

107
00:08:11,657 --> 00:08:14,327
[reporter] NLEA Chapel
has opened its doors to the public

108
00:08:14,410 --> 00:08:18,206
for those who wish to pay their respects
to the fallen members of Task Force Alpha.

109
00:08:18,289 --> 00:08:20,958
Among the TFA members lying in repose

110
00:08:21,042 --> 00:08:23,127
are those killed in the same hospital

111
00:08:23,211 --> 00:08:25,880
<i>where they were supposed to be recovering.</i>

112
00:08:25,963 --> 00:08:28,508
<i>They are Agent Oliver Lapeña,</i>

113
00:08:28,591 --> 00:08:32,845
<i>SPO Patrick Marquez,</i>
<i>and SPO2 Russel Contreras.</i>

114
00:08:32,929 --> 00:08:36,182
<i>NLEA has also put up a portrait</i>
<i>of Agent Harold Rustia,</i>

115
00:08:36,265 --> 00:08:37,683
<i>who died during their mission</i>

116
00:08:37,767 --> 00:08:40,144
<i>but whose body was not recovered.</i>

117
00:08:40,937 --> 00:08:43,356
<i>As of the moment,</i>
<i>authorities have no leads yet,</i>

118
00:08:43,439 --> 00:08:45,900
<i>but they are looking into the possibility</i>

119
00:08:45,983 --> 00:08:47,652
<i>that the suspect is connected</i>

120
00:08:47,735 --> 00:08:52,323
<i>to the syndicate involved</i>
<i>with gun smuggling suspect</i>

121
00:08:52,406 --> 00:08:54,158
<i>Datu Rahman Abubakar.</i>

122
00:08:54,242 --> 00:08:57,537
[morose music playing]

123
00:09:15,930 --> 00:09:21,018
[morose music continues]

124
00:09:52,633 --> 00:09:53,926
[boy] Papa!

125
00:09:55,094 --> 00:09:59,765
[sobbing, sniffling]

126
00:10:03,936 --> 00:10:07,607
[morose music continues]

127
00:10:12,612 --> 00:10:15,573
[sobs]

128
00:10:16,782 --> 00:10:17,867
Mrs. Lapeña?

129
00:10:19,118 --> 00:10:20,036
Stop crying now.

130
00:10:21,787 --> 00:10:22,955
Don't worry.

131
00:10:24,165 --> 00:10:26,959
I will find the person who did this.

132
00:10:27,043 --> 00:10:28,669
[tense music]

133
00:10:28,753 --> 00:10:33,424
Morals be damned, I promise you…

134
00:10:34,383 --> 00:10:35,968
that I will kill him.

135
00:10:37,011 --> 00:10:39,138
I will seek justice for your husband.

136
00:10:39,972 --> 00:10:41,307
[sobs]

137
00:10:41,390 --> 00:10:42,224
Just stay strong.

138
00:10:42,308 --> 00:10:46,979
[unsettling music playing]

139
00:10:50,650 --> 00:10:52,026
[sobs]

140
00:10:58,074 --> 00:11:00,409
[sobs]

141
00:11:03,913 --> 00:11:06,040
- [woman cries]
- [unsettling music continues]

142
00:11:18,886 --> 00:11:20,179
I know what you're thinking.

143
00:11:22,640 --> 00:11:24,100
You're blaming yourself.

144
00:11:28,145 --> 00:11:29,855
Marcus, get your head in the game.

145
00:11:30,773 --> 00:11:32,817
What happened to Oliver
and the others isn't your fault.

146
00:11:34,944 --> 00:11:37,780
The same way you're not to blame
for what happened to your brother.

147
00:11:44,620 --> 00:11:46,163
[sharp inhale] Don't go there, Lara.

148
00:11:46,247 --> 00:11:47,832
Look.

149
00:11:47,915 --> 00:11:50,000
If you really believe
you're being silenced,

150
00:11:50,626 --> 00:11:52,294
then find out the truth.

151
00:11:53,671 --> 00:11:54,922
Before it's too late.

152
00:11:56,799 --> 00:11:59,427
Unless you'd rather
waste your time being sad.

153
00:12:01,429 --> 00:12:03,305
Solve this, Marcus.

154
00:12:04,974 --> 00:12:06,392
For yourself.

155
00:12:10,521 --> 00:12:12,398
For our colleagues.

156
00:12:15,860 --> 00:12:19,905
[stirring music playing]

157
00:12:26,162 --> 00:12:30,040
[unsettling music playing]

158
00:12:56,400 --> 00:12:57,485
Coochie…

159
00:12:59,028 --> 00:12:59,904
Hello!

160
00:13:01,280 --> 00:13:02,364
Coochie!

161
00:13:05,493 --> 00:13:07,620
[melancholic music]

162
00:13:12,208 --> 00:13:13,918
My comrades were killed.

163
00:13:16,253 --> 00:13:17,880
Do you know who did it?

164
00:13:18,881 --> 00:13:21,258
I don't know what you're talking about.

165
00:13:21,342 --> 00:13:24,970
But you have information
on who killed them, right?

166
00:13:25,054 --> 00:13:27,806
[tense music playing]

167
00:13:27,890 --> 00:13:29,850
Answer me!

168
00:13:29,934 --> 00:13:31,519
I know you know something.

169
00:13:32,228 --> 00:13:34,772
I know someone is trying
to silence my group.

170
00:13:34,855 --> 00:13:37,525
Tell me who it is. Tell me!

171
00:13:40,027 --> 00:13:41,237
Again…

172
00:13:42,821 --> 00:13:45,241
I don't know what you're talking about.

173
00:13:45,324 --> 00:13:46,367
All I know is

174
00:13:46,450 --> 00:13:50,454
the person standing before me
is the man who led

175
00:13:51,121 --> 00:13:53,040
the massacre of my people!

176
00:13:53,123 --> 00:13:54,667
I didn't want that!

177
00:13:54,750 --> 00:13:56,710
I didn't want what happened that night!

178
00:13:59,713 --> 00:14:02,633
Just tell me what else you're hiding!

179
00:14:03,384 --> 00:14:05,094
- [slams table]
- Tell me the truth!

180
00:14:05,970 --> 00:14:07,930
[tense music continues]

181
00:14:08,514 --> 00:14:10,224
- [slams table]
- Ugh!

182
00:14:10,891 --> 00:14:12,726
[tense music]

183
00:14:15,563 --> 00:14:17,565
You'll get a lighter sentence…

184
00:14:19,149 --> 00:14:21,610
if you just cooperate with me.

185
00:14:39,044 --> 00:14:43,757
[morose music playing]

186
00:14:55,019 --> 00:14:56,437
[door clicks open]

187
00:15:06,697 --> 00:15:07,865
Agent Reyes.

188
00:15:09,783 --> 00:15:13,203
Why did you interrogate
a high-value suspect

189
00:15:13,913 --> 00:15:16,665
on your own and without permission?

190
00:15:16,749 --> 00:15:17,791
[sighs]

191
00:15:17,875 --> 00:15:19,501
I'm sorry, sir.

192
00:15:20,377 --> 00:15:22,379
I just had to find out the truth myself.

193
00:15:24,590 --> 00:15:27,593
All CCTV footage
that could point to the hitman

194
00:15:27,676 --> 00:15:30,804
who attacked my colleagues
has been wiped out.

195
00:15:31,388 --> 00:15:34,266
I wouldn't interrogate
a high-value suspect

196
00:15:34,850 --> 00:15:37,603
without following standard procedure
unless it were urgent, sir.

197
00:15:38,354 --> 00:15:40,147
Sir, this is obviously--

198
00:15:40,230 --> 00:15:42,566
That is obviously a hit!

199
00:15:43,609 --> 00:15:47,363
Your enemies retaliated
on the account of their leader,

200
00:15:47,446 --> 00:15:48,906
Datu Rahman!

201
00:15:48,989 --> 00:15:50,699
[stirring music continues]

202
00:15:50,783 --> 00:15:51,909
No, sir.

203
00:15:51,992 --> 00:15:53,994
- [tense music]
- [Azuelo] Anyway,

204
00:15:54,078 --> 00:15:55,996
the syndicate is now under investigation.

205
00:15:56,080 --> 00:15:56,956
No, sir.

206
00:15:57,039 --> 00:15:58,874
This wasn't revenge.

207
00:16:00,709 --> 00:16:02,920
They wanted to silence our group

208
00:16:03,003 --> 00:16:07,883
because they knew we were
holding valuable information.

209
00:16:09,259 --> 00:16:11,720
Valuable information
that could reveal the truth.

210
00:16:11,804 --> 00:16:13,138
Aside from my colleagues, he witnessed

211
00:16:13,222 --> 00:16:15,975
how everything went wrong
during the Zamboanga operation!

212
00:16:16,058 --> 00:16:18,394
What went wrong was that

213
00:16:18,477 --> 00:16:22,648
you massacred
innocent civilians in the area!

214
00:16:22,731 --> 00:16:24,817
The shoot-out happened, sir,

215
00:16:24,900 --> 00:16:27,903
because someone sabotaged our mission!

216
00:16:27,987 --> 00:16:32,408
Our operation was intercepted
on purpose, sir!

217
00:16:34,076 --> 00:16:35,995
That's why they wanted
to silence our group

218
00:16:36,078 --> 00:16:38,163
and killed my colleagues!

219
00:16:38,247 --> 00:16:39,498
That's the truth, sir!

220
00:16:39,581 --> 00:16:41,792
There you go again, Agent Reyes!

221
00:16:43,043 --> 00:16:47,256
You're changing the subject
!o cover up your mistakes!

222
00:16:48,882 --> 00:16:54,430
This is all happening
because of that damn bungled operation!

223
00:16:54,513 --> 00:16:57,182
And your team is taking the hit!

224
00:16:57,891 --> 00:16:59,643
Even the agency has been
dragged into this!

225
00:16:59,727 --> 00:17:02,104
And now the public is getting involved!

226
00:17:02,187 --> 00:17:04,857
They're saying that
Datu Rahman is innocent,

227
00:17:05,733 --> 00:17:08,152
and it's all because of you!

228
00:17:09,570 --> 00:17:11,321
[tense music playing]

229
00:17:23,542 --> 00:17:25,711
[Azuelo] Turn in your gun and badge.

230
00:17:27,046 --> 00:17:30,883
I'll give them back to you
as soon as your suspension is over.

231
00:17:31,467 --> 00:17:34,178
For now, take a break, Agent Reyes.

232
00:17:34,928 --> 00:17:36,597
And this is for your own good.

233
00:17:37,264 --> 00:17:41,060
[morose music playing]

234
00:17:58,077 --> 00:18:01,205
[tense music]

235
00:18:02,331 --> 00:18:06,043
[stirring music playing]

236
00:18:23,519 --> 00:18:29,441
[stirring music continues]

237
00:18:39,409 --> 00:18:44,206
[somber music playing]

238
00:19:20,576 --> 00:19:25,414
[music becomes dramatic]

239
00:19:45,017 --> 00:19:47,060
[Jalil] <i>I'm going to set things right.</i>

240
00:19:47,144 --> 00:19:50,189
<i>I'm sure Father is innocent.</i>

241
00:19:50,272 --> 00:19:53,483
<i>They only place the blame on us</i>
<i>because we're easy targets.</i>

242
00:19:53,567 --> 00:19:55,235
‪[melancholic music playing]

243
00:19:55,319 --> 00:19:56,528
[Marcus] <i>This is no ordinary group.</i>

244
00:19:56,612 --> 00:19:58,071
And they won't stop

245
00:19:58,155 --> 00:20:00,157
until they erase all the evidence.

246
00:20:00,240 --> 00:20:01,742
So what are you implying, Marcus?

247
00:20:01,825 --> 00:20:03,660
I know who the next target is.

248
00:20:03,744 --> 00:20:04,828
Who?

249
00:20:04,912 --> 00:20:07,289
We will move our high-profile detainee

250
00:20:07,372 --> 00:20:09,124
to a more secure facility.

251
00:20:09,208 --> 00:20:10,334
[man] <i>You're a Muslim, aren't you?</i>

252
00:20:10,417 --> 00:20:13,629
<i>I hope you're not planning</i>
<i>on helping Datu Rahman escape.</i>

253
00:20:13,712 --> 00:20:17,507
<i>You're a policeman.</i>
<i>You should never side with criminals.</i>

254
00:20:17,591 --> 00:20:20,135
[activists] <i>Justice! Justice!</i>
<i>We want justice!</i>

255
00:20:20,219 --> 00:20:24,264
Justice! Justice!

256
00:20:24,348 --> 00:20:25,182
All units, formation check.

257
00:20:25,265 --> 00:20:27,809
High-value detainee exiting.
Maintain perimeter.

258
00:20:27,893 --> 00:20:30,520
[female activist] <i>Justice for Zamboanga!</i>

259
00:20:30,604 --> 00:20:31,730
<i>Freedom for Datu Rahman!</i>

260
00:20:31,813 --> 00:20:34,107
[activists chanting] Justice!

261
